
------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.48 (2014.04.03)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- deadtime counter fix (m_count.vhd)
- tt_dump for incoming serial data (see statft and reg #9f0)
- fix the case with latency=0x3ffff

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.49 (2014.04.07)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- olinkdn flag is added (still need to sort out)

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.50 (2014.04.14)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- crc8 checksum test for b2tt uplink (from fee to ft2u) for b2tt0.15

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.52 (2014.04.18)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- status bit rearrangement (statft is not fully updated yet)
- TTCMD_RST rearrangement for b2lreset / gtpreset

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.53 (2014.05.05)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- clock to ttrx5 is also sent at o_rsv, for tt5r020

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.54 (2014.06.27)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- chipscope attached for the first time

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.55 (2014.07.09)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- chipscope signal assignment is modified
- tagdiff is negated
- crc8 is added also in the ft2u -> FEE direction

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.56 (2014.07.15)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- stareset is added to reset FEE errors without issuing a runreset

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.57 (2014.07.18)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- ttrxrst is implemented instead of autorst, to use FTSW without a CPU
  control.  Now AUX 5-4 pair can be used to reset FTSW from TT-RX.  This
  feature is disabled when FTSW FPGA is programmed by bootft.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.58 (2014.07.27)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- command and address definition changed, not compatible with b2tt-0.28
  - two serial streams for nominal and masked ports
  - these streams can be switched without breaking disparity
  - disparity control packet is added to absorb the disparity difference

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.59 (2014.07.28)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- fix of disparity control
- OUT-16 was used for special purpose since ft2u-0.44, now it behaves
  like other JTAG port

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.60 (2014.08.04)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- block JTAG write mode

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.61 (2014.08.10)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- iscan based idelay adjustment for all ports

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.62 (2014.08.10)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- tt_phasedet fix, more thorough chipscope signal definitions

------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 0.63 (2014.08.11)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- crc error debug, which did not show up before receiving fast busy from
  ft2x (not applicable to ttrx-ports, and fee doesn't usually generate
  busy)

- to be used with ft2x012, ft3d004, as well as other b2tt-0.29 fee and
  tt4r021/tt5r021.

- there's still room to improve reset procedure.

- crc error detection code may not be perfect, need to examine with a
  simulator.
